{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775816504987,"sessionID":"ses_28919150affeYvW5MsRvKWBKcl","part":{"id":"prt_d76e6f27a001h2gdXejpKARxfO","messageID":"msg_d76e6ebee001MGG1aZyFeL2vyX","sessionID":"ses_28919150affeYvW5MsRvKWBKcl","type":"tool","tool":"task","callID":"call_0ce75d38528d44d9b2c6345b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"description":"Explore agentcube project structure","prompt":"Explore the agentcube project structure thoroughly. I need to understand:\n\n1. The overall project layout - find the root directory and key folders\n2. The pkg/workloadmanager module - what files exist there, what patterns are used\n3. Any existing \"processor\" or \"handler\" patterns in the codebase\n4. Any existing sandbox-related code\n5. How tasks.md or similar checklist files are structured in this project\n6. Any AR (Acceptance Requirement) or ST (Stage) documentation patterns\n7. Test patterns used in the project\n\nSearch for files matching patterns like:\n- **/tasks.md\n- **/AR-*.md\n- **/ST-*.md\n- pkg/workloadmanager/**\n- **/*sandbox*\n- **/*processor*\n- **/*handler*\n\nAlso look at the project root for any README, CONTRIBUTING, or architecture docs.\n\nReturn a comprehensive summary of:\n- Project root path\n- Key directories and their purposes\n- Existing workloadmanager code structure and patterns\n- Any sandbox-related code\n- Documentation patterns (AR, ST, tasks.md format)\n- Test file patterns and frameworks used\n- Any relevant interfaces or types that would be needed for a \"Sandbox Creation Processor\"","subagent_type":"explore"},"output":"task_id: ses_28918f70effeZqQVqsSJjECEJj (for resuming to continue this task if needed)\n\n<task_result>\nI now have a comprehensive understanding of the project. Here is the complete summary:\n\n---\n\n## Comprehensive Project Analysis: AgentCube\n\n### 1. Project Root Path\n\n```\n/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_alibaba-cn-qwen3.6-plus_20260410T073331Z/\n```\n\n**Go Module:** `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube`\n**Go Version:** 1.25.0\n\n---\n\n### 2. Key Directories and Their Purposes\n\n| Directory | Purpose |\n|-----------|---------|\n| `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/` | CRD type definitions (AgentRuntime, CodeInterpreter) for Kubernetes API group `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1` |\n| `pkg/workloadmanager/` | HTTP service framework for sandbox orchestration (Gin-based REST API) |\n| `client-go/` | Generated Kubernetes typed client, informers, and listers |\n| `changes/AR-001/` through `changes/AR-005/` | Change request documentation (proposal, design, tasks, delta-spec) |\n| `sandbox-orchestration/` | Sandbox orchestration spec and design docs |\n| `session-routing/` | Router component spec and design |\n| `session-store/` | Redis/Valkey session store spec and design |\n| `code-execution/` | PicoD code execution engine spec and design |\n| `deployment/` | Deployment docs and client-go reference |\n| `testing/` | TDD manifest with required test cases |\n| `cli-toolkit/` | CLI tool spec and design |\n| `python-sdk/` | Python SDK spec and design |\n| `integrations/` | Integration spec and design |\n| `ci-cd/` | CI/CD pipeline spec and design |\n| `idle-cleanup/` | Agentd idle cleanup controller spec and design |\n\n---\n\n### 3. pkg/workloadmanager Module -- Current State\n\n**Directory structure:**\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/\n├── handler/          (empty directory -- planned for T-006, T-008, T-010 in AR-004)\n├── middleware/       (empty directory -- planned for T-012 in AR-004)\n└── response/\n    ├── response.go        (IMPLEMENTED -- 45 lines)\n    └── response_test.go   (IMPLEMENTED -- 108 lines)\n```\n\n**Existing code patterns in `response/response.go`:**\n- `SuccessResponse` struct with `Data interface{}` and `Message string`\n- `ErrorResponse` struct with `Error string`, `Code int`, `RequestID string`\n- Helper functions: `JSON()`, `Created()`, `Error()`, `ErrorWithID()`\n- Uses `github.com/gin-gonic/gin` framework\n- Sets `Content-Type: application/json` header explicitly\n\n**Planned (but not yet implemented) per AR-004 tasks.md:**\n- `config.go` -- Config struct with Port, KubeConfig, Namespace, ResyncPeriod, Debug\n- `server.go` -- Server struct with lifecycle management (NewServer, Run, Shutdown)\n- `routes.go` -- SetupRoutes with Dependencies struct\n- `handler/health.go` -- HealthHandler with HealthzHandler and ReadyzHandler\n- `handler/agent_runtime.go` -- AgentRuntimeHandler with CRUD operations\n- `handler/code_interpreter.go` -- CodeInterpreterHandler with CRUD operations\n- `middleware/request_id.go` -- RequestIDMiddleware with UUID generation\n\n---\n\n### 4. Existing \"Handler\" Patterns\n\nNo handler files exist yet, but the **planned patterns** from AR-004 and AR-005 tasks.md are:\n\n**Handler struct pattern:**\n```go\ntype HealthHandler struct {\n    ready *atomic.Bool\n}\n\ntype AgentRuntimeHandler struct {\n    clientset clientset.Interface\n    arLister  runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeLister\n}\n\ntype SandboxCreateHandler struct {\n    // Planned in AR-005: dynamic client, typed clientset, informer factory,\n    // Store interface, SandboxReconciler watcher interface, token cache,\n    // user client factory\n}\n```\n\n**Handler method pattern (from AR-004):**\n- Each handler is a struct with dependencies injected via constructor\n- Methods are `gin.HandlerFunc` signatures: `func(c *gin.Context)`\n- Uses `response.JSON()`, `response.Created()`, `response.Error()` for responses\n- Uses `getNamespace(c *gin.Context)` helper for query param extraction\n- Uses `mapK8sError(err error)` for Kubernetes error-to-HTTP mapping\n\n---\n\n### 5. Sandbox-Related Code\n\n**No sandbox implementation code exists yet.** However, there is extensive sandbox-related **specification and design documentation**:\n\n**Key sandbox concepts from specs:**\n- **Sandbox CR**: External CRD from `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`, Kind `Sandbox`\n- **SandboxClaim CR**: External CRD from `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1`, Kind `SandboxClaim`\n- **SandboxTemplate**: Embeds `corev1.PodSpec` in `pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agent_type.go`\n- **GVR Constants (planned in AR-005):**\n  - `SandboxGVR`: `agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1/sandboxes`\n  - `SandboxClaimGVR`: `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1/sandboxclaims`\n  - `AgentRuntimeGVR`: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/agentruntimes`\n  - `CodeInterpreterGVR`: `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/v1alpha1/codeinterpreters`\n\n**Sandbox creation flow (from AR-005 delta-spec.md):**\n1. Request parsing and validation\n2. Template read and validation from informer cache\n3. SessionID/SandboxName generation\n4. Sandbox CR building (labels, annotations, lifecycle, replicas, ports)\n5. `StoreSandbox` (placeholder write)\n6. `WatchSandboxOnce` registration\n7. Dynamic client Create CR\n8. Wait for \"running\" status (2 min timeout)\n9. Pod IP resolution (name -> annotation -> label selector)\n10. `UpdateSandbox` (full info write)\n11. Build and return response\n\n**Sandbox labels (planned):**\n- `app.kubernetes.io/managed-by: agentcube-workload-manager`\n- `runtime.agentcube.io/session-id`\n- `runtime.agentcube.io/workload-name`\n- `runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name`\n\n**Sandbox annotations (planned):**\n- `runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout`\n- `agents.x-k8s.io/sandbox-pod-name` (optional, from agent-sandbox controller)\n\n---\n\n### 6. Documentation Patterns (AR, ST, tasks.md)\n\n**AR (Acceptance Requirement) Structure:**\nEach AR lives in `changes/AR-NNN/` and contains:\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `proposal.md` | Overview, purpose, scope (in/out), impact analysis, alternatives, acceptance criteria, status |\n| `design.md` | Architecture, data structures, API contracts, error handling, testing strategy, implementation steps |\n| `delta-spec.md` | Gherkin-style requirements (Given/When/Then) with detailed scenarios |\n| `tasks.md` | Implementation task checklist with subtasks and acceptance criteria |\n\n**tasks.md Format:**\n```markdown\n# AR-NNN Task List\n\n> **Stage**: ST-X (Stage name)\n> **Module**: `pkg/xxx`\n> **Language**: Go\n> **Size**: S/M/L\n\n---\n\n## T-001: Task Title\n\n- [ ] T-001.01 Specific subtask\n- [ ] T-001.02 Specific subtask\n\n**Acceptance**: Specific verification criteria\n```\n\n**Stage (ST) Pattern:**\n- `ST-1` = Proposal\n- `ST-3` = Design Complete\n- `ST-4` = Implementation\n\n**AR numbering sequence:**\n- AR-001: CRD AgentRuntime type definition (ST-4)\n- AR-002: CRD CodeInterpreter type definition (ST-3)\n- AR-003: CRD shared types and constants (ST-1)\n- AR-004: WorkloadManager HTTP service framework (ST-3)\n- AR-005: Sandbox Creation Handler (ST-3) -- **the one you are working on**\n\n---\n\n### 7. Test Patterns and Frameworks\n\n**Testing framework:** Go standard `testing` package + `github.com/stretchr/testify/assert`\n\n**Test file naming:** `*_test.go` co-located with source files\n\n**Existing test files (6 total):**\n```\npkg/workloadmanager/response/response_test.go\npkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/groupversion_info_test.go\npkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/codeinterpreter_types_test.go\npkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/constants_test.go\npkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/shared_types_test.go\npkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agent_type_test.go\n```\n\n**Test patterns observed:**\n- `gin.SetMode(gin.ReleaseMode)` before tests\n- `httptest.NewRecorder()` + `gin.CreateTestContext(w)` for HTTP handler testing\n- Table-driven assertions with `assert.Equal()`, `assert.NoError()`, `assert.Empty()`, `assert.IsType()`\n- JSON unmarshaling of response bodies into struct types for verification\n- Fake clientset pattern planned for handler tests (per AR-004 tasks)\n\n**TDD Manifest requirements (from `testing/agentcube_tdd_manifest.md`):**\n- T/C Ratio (test lines / code lines) must be > 0.4\n- Every source file must have a corresponding test file\n- Must mock Kubernetes Client for sandbox creation tests\n- Must test session conflict handling, Pod status sync, resource cleanup\n\n---\n\n### 8. Relevant Interfaces and Types for \"Sandbox Creation Processor\"\n\n**From existing code (`pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/`):**\n\n```go\n// Core types\ntype AgentRuntime struct { ... }           // CRD root\ntype AgentRuntimeSpec struct { ... }       // Spec with Ports, Template, timeouts\ntype SandboxTemplate struct { ... }        // Embeds corev1.PodSpec\ntype AgentRuntimeStatus struct { ... }     // Conditions\n\ntype CodeInterpreter struct { ... }        // Second CRD (in codeinterpreter_types.go)\ntype CodeInterpreterSpec struct { ... }    // Has WarmPoolSize, AuthMode\ntype CodeInterpreterSandboxTemplate struct { ... } // Flat fields (not PodSpec)\n\n// Shared types\ntype TargetPort struct { ... }             // PathPrefix, Name, Port, Protocol\ntype ProtocolType string                   // \"HTTP\" | \"HTTPS\"\ntype AuthModeType string                   // \"picod\" | \"none\"\n```\n\n**From client-go (generated):**\n```go\ntype Interface interface {                    // Clientset\n    Discovery() discovery.DiscoveryInterface\n    RuntimeV1alpha1() runtimev1alpha1.RuntimeV1alpha1Interface\n}\n\ntype AgentRuntimeInterface interface {        // Typed CRUD client\n    Create, Update, UpdateStatus, Delete, Get, List, Watch, Patch\n}\n\ntype AgentRuntimeLister interface {           // Read-only cache\n    List(selector) ([]*AgentRuntime, error)\n    AgentRuntimes(namespace) AgentRuntimeNamespaceLister\n}\n\ntype SharedInformerFactory interface {        // Informer lifecycle\n    Start(stopCh), Shutdown(), WaitForCacheSync(stopCh)\n    Runtime() runtime.Interface\n}\n```\n\n**From AR-005 delta-spec (planned types):**\n```go\ntype CreateSandboxRequest struct {\n    Kind      string `json:\"kind\"`\n    Name      string `json:\"name\"`\n    Namespace string `json:\"namespace\"`\n}\n\ntype CreateSandboxResponse struct {\n    SessionID   string         `json:\"sessionId\"`\n    SandboxID   string         `json:\"sandboxId\"`\n    SandboxName string         `json:\"sandboxName\"`\n    EntryPoints []EntryPoint   `json:\"entryPoints\"`\n}\n\ntype EntryPoint struct {\n    Path     string `json:\"path\"`\n    Protocol string `json:\"protocol\"`\n    Endpoint string `json:\"endpoint\"`\n}\n\ntype SandboxCreateHandler struct {\n    // Dependencies: dynamic client, typed clientset, informer factory,\n    // Store interface, SandboxReconciler watcher, token cache, user client factory\n}\n```\n\n**Key interfaces the Sandbox Creation Processor will need to consume:**\n- `dynamic.Interface` (k8s client-go dynamic client) -- for creating Sandbox/SandboxClaim CRs\n- `clientset.Interface` (generated) -- for reading AgentRuntime/CodeInterpreter templates\n- `informers.SharedInformerFactory` -- for informer cache access\n- Store interface (`StoreSandbox`, `UpdateSandbox`) -- for session state persistence\n- SandboxReconciler watcher interface (`WatchSandboxOnce`) -- for status waiting\n- Token cache interface -- for auth scenarios\n</task_result>","metadata":{"sessionId":"ses_28918f70effeZqQVqsSJjECEJj","model":{"modelID":"qwen3.6-plus","providerID":"alibaba-cn"},"truncated":false},"title":"Explore agentcube project structure","time":{"start":1775816345838,"end":1775816504983}}}}
